full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/1 1/2023 JOHN C. DeMOCKER, M.D., P.C. 564 RIDGE ROAD EAST ROCHESTER, NEW YORK 14621 - Telephone 544-1750 September 26, 1972 PATIENT: MEHTA, Savitri 226355 HISTORY: Routine chest survey for immigration purposes. X -RAY: Chest: PA view in the upright position demonstrate no acute cardio-pulmonary abnormality. There was slight linear scarring in both peri-hilar areas. The heart and mediastinum were within normal limits. The osseous and soft tissue structures of the thoracic cage area were intact. IMPRESSION: No significant abnormality. There was slight peri-bronchial scarring bilaterally. John C. DeMocker, M.D. JCd/gss
